template.name: Template WSFC for preprocessing
template.description:
Windows Server Failover Cluster Template Tested on Windows Server 2008 R2 SP1, Windows Server 2012 R2, Windows Server 2016, Zabbix v 2.4.
https://github.com/zbx-sadman/WSFC
Requirement: wsfc.ps1 v.1.2.4

trigger_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] Network interface {#NAME} is unavailable by ICMP
[{#CLUSTER}] On network interface {#NAME} ping loss is too high
[{#CLUSTER}] On network interface {#NAME} response time is too high

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] Network {#NAME} role
item_prototype.description:
Role of the network in the cluster.
0 - ClusterNetworkRoleNone The network is not used by the cluster.
1 - ClusterNetworkRoleInternalUse The network is used to carry internal cluster communication.
2 - ClusterNetworkRoleClientAccess Not supported.
3 - ClusterNetworkRoleInternalAndClient The network is used to connect client systems and to carry internal cluster communication.

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] Node {#NAME} assigned (used) memory
item_prototype.description: The total of current memory usage of the virtual systems on clusternode.

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] Node {#NAME} assigned vCPUs
item_prototype.description: The total number of virtual processors allocated to the virtual systems on clusternode.

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] Node {#NAME} processor load
item_prototype.description: The total current processor usage of the virtual systems on clusternode.

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] GS {#NAME} persistent state
item_prototype.description: Specifies whether the resource should be brought online or left offline when the Cluster service is started.

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] GS {#NAME} restart action
item_prototype.description:
0 - ClusterResourceDontRestart Do not restart the resource after a failure.
1 - ClusterResourceRestartNoNotify Restart the resource after a failure. If the resource exceeds its restart threshold within its restart period, do not attempt to failover the group to another node in the cluster.
2 - ClusterResourceRestartNotify Restart the resource after a failure. If the resource exceeds its restart threshold within its restart period, attempt to fail over the group to another node in the cluster. This is the default setting.

trigger_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] IP address {#NAME} is unavailable by ICMP
[{#CLUSTER}] IP address {#NAME} ping loss is too high
[{#CLUSTER}] IP address {#NAME} response time is too high

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] Physical disk {#NAME} CSV enforce writethrough
item_prototype.description:
Controls the write-through caching policy of a physical disk resource on a cluster shared volume.
Minimum supported server: Windows Server 2012
0 - Do not add write-through. 1 - Add write-through to all down-level I/O sent by direct I/O. 2 - Add write-through to all down-level I/O sent by direct I/O and harden the virtual desktop infrastructure (VDl) on a write-through file object. 3 - Add write-through to all down-level I/O sent by direct I/O, harden the virtual desktop infrastructure (VDl) on a write-through file object, and ensure that top-level files are always opened for write-through.

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] Physical disk {#NAME} enable block cache
item_prototype.description:
Minimum supported server: Windows Server 2012
https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/jj151967(v=vs.85).aspx

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] Physical disk {#NAME} virtual disk health
item_prototype.description:
Specifies the health of the virtual disk.
Minimum supported server: Windows Server 2012
0 - The health of the virtual disk is unknown. 1 - The virtual disk is unhealthy. 2 - The virtual disk has a health warning.. 3 - The virtual disk is healthy. 4 - This is the maximum value.

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] Physical disk {#NAME} virtual disk provisioning
item_prototype.description:
Specifies the provisioning type of the virtual disk.
Minimum supported server: Windows Server 2012
0 - The provisioning type of the virtual disk is unknown. 1 - The virtual disk contains thin provisioning. 2 - The virtual disk contains fixed provisioning. 3 - TBD

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] Physical disk {#NAME} virtual disk resiliency type
item_prototype.description:
Specifies the resiliency type of the virtual disk.
Minimum supported server: Windows Server 2012
0 - The resiliency type of the virtual disk is unknown. 1 - The virtual disk has a simple resiliency type. 2 - The virtual disk has a mirror resiliency type. 3 - The virtual disk has a parity resiliency type. 4 - Maximum value.

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] SQL Server {#INSTANCENAME} failure condition level
item_prototype.description:
The FailureConditionLevel property defines which detected health statuses cause restarts or failovers.
https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/sql/sql-server/failover-clusters/windows/failover-policy-for-failover-cluster-instances#determine
0 - No automatic failover or restart 1 - Failover or restart on server down 2 - Failover or restart on server unresponsive 3* - Failover or restart on critical server errors 4 - Failover or restart on moderate server errors 5 - Failover or restart on any qualified failure conditions
*Default Value

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] SQL Server {#INSTANCENAME} SqlDumper dump path
item_prototype.description:
The location where the SQLDumper utility generates the dump files.
https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/sql/relational-databases/system-dynamic-management-views/sys-dm-os-cluster-properties-transact-sql

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] SQL Server {#INSTANCENAME} verbose logging
item_prototype.description:
The logging level for the SQL Server failover cluster. Verbose logging can be turned on to provide additional details in the error logs for troubleshooting. One of the following values:
https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/sql/relational-databases/system-dynamic-management-views/sys-dm-os-cluster-properties-transact-sql
0 – Logging is turned off (default) 1 - Errors only 2 – Errors and warnings

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] VM {#NAME} check heartbeat
item_prototype.description:
Indicates whether the heartbeat of the virtual machine (VM) should be used to determine the health of the VM.
0 - Don't Check Heartbeat (Default) The heartbeat is not checked.
1 - Check Heartbeat The heartbeat is checked; if the heartbeat fails, a resource failure is signaled.

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] VM {#NAME} migration failure reason
item_prototype.description:
Provides the HRESULT that details the reason for a failed live migration.
0 - S_OK (Default) The migration completed successfully.
0x800700AA - E_BUSY The migration failed because another migration was in progress.
0x80004005 - E_FAIL The migration failed for some other reason.

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] VM {#NAME} migration progress
item_prototype.description: The estimated percentage of the completion of the migration.

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] VM {#NAME} migration state
item_prototype.description:
0 - No (Default) No migration is in progress.
1 - Setup The migration of the VM was started and the setup of the migration is in progress.
2 - Data Transfer The VM data (including the contents of the VM memory) is being transferred to the target node.
3 - Move The move of the VM resource group is in progress.
4 - Canceled An earlier migration attempt was canceled.
5 - Failure An earlier migration attempt failed. The MigrationState property will retain this value until it is reset or another migration is started.

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] VM {#NAME} offline action
item_prototype.description:
0 - Turn Off The VM is turned off.
1 - Save (Default) The VM is saved.
2 - Shutdown The guest operating system running in the VM is shut down. This requires that the guest operating system has the shutdown integration component installed.
3 - Shutdown (Forced) The Windows guest operating system running in the VM is shut down forcibly.

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] VM {#NAME} start memory
item_prototype.description:
Minimum supported server: Windows Server 2012
https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/jj151996(v=vs.85).aspx

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] VM {#NAME} virtual NUMA count
item_prototype.description:
Minimum supported server: Windows Server 2012
https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/jj151997(v=vs.85).aspx

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] VM {#NAME} vmState
item_prototype.description:
0 - Unknown (Default) The state of the VM could not be determined.
2 - Enabled The VM is running.
3 - Disabled The VM is turned off.
32768 - Paused The VM is paused.
32769 - Suspended The VM is in a saved state.
32770 - Starting The VM is starting.
32773 - Saving The VM is saving its state.
32774 - Stopping The VM is turning off.
32776 - Pausing The VM is pausing.
32777 - Resuming The VM is resuming from a paused state.

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] VM {#NAME} persistent state
item_prototype.description: Specifies whether the resource should be brought online or left offline when the Cluster service is started.

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] VM {#NAME} restart action
item_prototype.description:
0 - ClusterResourceDontRestart Do not restart the resource after a failure.
1 - ClusterResourceRestartNoNotify Restart the resource after a failure. If the resource exceeds its restart threshold within its restart period, do not attempt to failover the group to another node in the cluster.
2 - ClusterResourceRestartNotify Restart the resource after a failure. If the resource exceeds its restart threshold within its restart period, attempt to fail over the group to another node in the cluster. This is the default setting.

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] VM {#NAME} heartbeat
item_prototype.description:
The current heartbeat status for the virtual system.
2 - OK 6 - Error 12 - No Contact 13 - Lost Communication

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] CSV {#NAME} block level redirected reason
item_prototype.description:
https://blogs.msdn.microsoft.com/clustering/2014/03/13/cluster-shared-volume-diagnostics/
Minimum supported server: Windows Server 2012
NoDiskConnectivity – Disk is not visible on/connected to this node. You need to validate your SAN settings.
StorageSpaceNotAttached – Space is not attached on this node.

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] CSV {#NAME} fle system redirected reason
item_prototype.description:
https://blogs.msdn.microsoft.com/clustering/2014/03/13/cluster-shared-volume-diagnostics/
Minimum supported server: Windows Server 2012
UserRequest – user put volume in redirected state.
IncompatibleFileSystemFilter – An incompatible file system filter attached to the NTFS/REFS file system.
IncompatibleVolumeFilter – An incompatible volume filter attached below NTFS/REFS.
FileSystemTiering – Volume is in file system redirected mode because the volume is a Tiered Space with heatmap tracking enabled.
BitLockerInitializing – Volume is in redirected state because we are waiting for BitLocker to finish initial volume encryption of this volume.

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] CSV {#NAME} fault state
item_prototype.description:
Returns the fault state of the cluster shared volume.
https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/ee342510(v=vs.85).aspx
0 - No Faults (NoFaults) 1 - Redirected Access (NoDirectIO) 2 - No Access (NoAccess) 4 - In Maintenance (Maintenence)

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] CSV {#NAME} free space
item_prototype.description: Provides the total space available for the partition, in megabytes (megabytes or bytes?)

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] CSV {#NAME} NTFS is compressed
item_prototype.description: NTFS volume is compressed or not

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] CSV {#NAME} NTFS dirty flag
item_prototype.description: When the Dirty Flag is set (volume corruption detected), Windows must perform the chkdsk/F command on the volume when it next boots.

item_prototype.name: [{#CLUSTER}] CSV {#NAME} NTFS partition number is valid
[{#CLUSTER}] CSV {#NAME} NTFS partition size is valid
[{#CLUSTER}] CSV {#NAME} StateInfo
item_prototype.description:
See BlockRedirectedIOReason & FileSystemRedirectedIOReason metrics for get reasons
Minimum supported server: Windows Server 2012

item_prototype.name: [{#NAME}] BackupInProgress
item_prototype.description: Indicates whether or not a Volume Shadow Copy Service Task is currently in progress for a specific volume on the cluster

item_prototype.name: [{#NAME}] FixQuorum
item_prototype.description: Specifies if the cluster is in a fix quorum state

item_prototype.name: [{#NAME}] IPSec disabled for inter-node cluster communication
item_prototype.description:
Specifies whether Internet Protocol Security (IPSec) encryption is enabled for inter-node cluster communication.
!!! "0" enables IPSec, "1" disables it.
https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dn765665(v=vs.85).aspx

item_prototype.name: [{#NAME}] Shutdown Timeout (min)
item_prototype.description: Specifies how many minutes after a system shutdown is initiated that the failover cluster service will wait for resources to go offline.

item_prototype.name: [{#NAME}] Witness restart interval (min)
item_prototype.description: When using a Node and File Share Majority quorum mode, specifies how long (in minutes) the system will wait before attempting to restart a failed file share witness resource.

item_prototype.name: [{#NAME}] Assigned (Used) Memory
item_prototype.description: The total of current memory usage of the virtual systems on cluster.

item_prototype.name: [{#NAME}] Assigned vCPUs
item_prototype.description: The total number of virtual processors allocated to the virtual systems on cluster.
